    "title": "Foundation: Naming and Pointing",
    "explanation": "This chapter introduces character names and basic nouns. In Japanese, a single noun can be a complete utterance: 船。(A boat.) needs no verb. Characters identify themselves with わたし、X。(I [am] X.) — the comma marks a pause that equates two things without any grammar word. You will also encounter basic demonstratives like pointing at things and naming them.",
